     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">The northern suburb that families pursue when they want large blocks and quiet streets close to the city, with Ferny Grove rail access and a settled residential character that the busier northern addresses no longer offer.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Keperra sits approximately twelve kilometres north-west of the Brisbane CBD, tucked between Mitchelton, Gaythorne, and Ferny Grove in the northern corridor that draws families in search of space, quiet streets, and a genuine community feel. The suburb is defined by its large residential blocks, its established streetscapes, and its position as the right answer for families who have been comparing the northern corridor and want more land than the tighter Mitchelton and Gaythorne addresses provide. Those buyers arrive in Keperra having already researched the corridor. They know the Ferny Grove line, they know what the school catchments look like, and they have concluded that Keperra delivers the northern Brisbane lifestyle with the block size they are looking for.
    </p>
