    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Keperra.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Keperra?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Keperra values are driven by block size, street position within the suburb, access to the Ferny Grove rail line, and the school catchments that attract family buyers to the northern corridor. The suburb sits at a price point below the tighter Mitchelton and Gaythorne addresses, which creates consistent demand from families who want more land and quieter streets while staying connected to the CBD by rail. Properties on well-positioned streets with larger lots and good street appeal attract the strongest buyer competition.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Keperra?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Keperra homes typically sell within 28 to 42 days. Buyers who target this suburb have usually been comparing the northern corridor and arrived at Keperra specifically for the larger land parcels. When a suitable property appears at an accurate price, those buyers are ready to act. Autumn and spring produce the strongest campaigns, but family buyers committed to the northern corridor maintain interest throughout the year.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Keperra?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Keperra offers a quiet, family-oriented lifestyle about twelve kilometres north-west of the Brisbane CBD. The suburb is defined by its large blocks, established street trees, and the outdoor lifestyle that generous land provides. The Ferny Grove rail line provides CBD connections, and Mitchelton's Blackwood Street precinct is nearby for everyday dining and retail. It is a suburb where families come for space and quiet, and the owner-occupier character creates a genuinely settled community.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Keperra a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Keperra offers genuine opportunity for families who want more land than the tighter northern suburb addresses provide. The suburb delivers generous blocks, rail access, quiet streets, and school catchments at a price point that reflects its position one step from the most sought-after corridor addresses. Its low turnover and consistent demand from well-researched family buyers make it a sound long-term owner-occupier consideration for anyone committed to the northern Brisbane lifestyle.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

